    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Eustis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have yours of yesterday. It does not answer mine of 16th upon point whether
                    pardon on terms specified by French Government will be acceptable to Waller.
                    Please report on that point at earliest practicable moment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
